description: For sale: $359,900. This is a MUST SEE if you are looking for a true warehouse conversion with character & an unbeatable location in Downtown Minneapolis North Loop just one block from the Mississippi River. Upon entering you will find a beautiful open floor plan with European engineered oak hardwood flooring throughout, exposed brick walls and solid timber beams, & 10.5 foot ceilings. The large, architectural cathedral-style windows flood the entire unit with natural light. The updated kitchen boasts cherry hardwood cabinets, center island, stainless steel appliances & updated lighting. The bathroom has been completely renovated & expanded and includes marble countertop, cherry cabinets, ceramic tile floor & European style combination washer/dryer. The spacious master bedroom includes direct access to the bathroom & a newly expanded walk-in closet with built-in closet organizer. The recently added second bedroom is located on the opposite end of the living room for added privacy. Rare corner unit!

description: For sale: $424,900. Beautiful 2 bed, 2 bath condo in coveted 5th Ave Lofts. Wide open floor plan with floor to ceiling windows and a Juliet balcony bring in tons of natural light. Updated kitchen includes stainless steel appliances, granite countertops and a subway tile backsplash. Master bedroom includes a walk through closet to a large, full bathroom. 2nd bedroom sits near the 3/4 bathroom and houses the in-unit laundry. Live among the best restaurants the Twin Cities has to offer, just blocks from the River and Stone Arch Bridge.

For sale: $1,125,000. This penthouse-class Bookmen Stacks loft masterfully designed by celebrity architect James Dayton presents maximum views in comfort and quiet. 2020 renovations just completed! Floor-to-ceiling windows wrap around three sides, soaking in the sparkling skyline; captivating views east, south and west. Gleaming concrete floors & 11' ceilings; sleek & sexy gourmet kitchen featuring Wolf, Sub-Zero & Asko; private dining rm open to the city lights; fabulous owner's suite boasts a magnificent skyline view, expansive dressing rm & luxurious bath.  2nd suite is perfect for guests or media. Breathtaking balcony overlooks the lush courtyard. Perfect North Loop location in the heart of the action - best restaurants, bars, theatre, sports and Target Field light rail right out your door! Two prime underground spaces, 96 & 97, + guest parking. All-inclusive association fee; roof-top gym & outdoor party deck with fireplace. Dramatic city colors & sunsets. Fast access in & out of downtown. Have it all!

Coming soon: $750,000. Fantastic North Loop townhouse with tasteful finishes in a gorgeous setting. Features include fireplace with built-ins, oversized owner's suite with sitting area, deck and two walk-in closets. Owner's bath with walk-in shower, heated floors and granite vanity top with under-mount sinks. Renovated eat-in kitchen with upgraded appliances and deck for grilling. Updated bathrooms and lower level bathroom rough-in for a 4th. Recent improvements include garage door and opener, hardwood flooring, carpeting, painting and lighting. All new Anderson windows and deck door. Steps to the riverfront, and near the city's best dining, shopping and entertainment.

Coming soon: $389,900. Gorgeous two level condo with stunning finishes throughout. Hardwood flooring, 3 sided fireplace w/ marble surround, smooth ceilings, enameled millwork & new door hardware. Upgraded mechanicals include new furnace, humidifier & water heater. New appliances include washer, dryer, refrigerator, range, disposal & microwave. Kitchen with granite, marble backsplash, Kohler sink & touchless faucet. Bathroom w/ stunning tile work & Restoration Hardware fixtures. Courtyard views in a fantastic North Loop location.

description: For sale: $289,900. Stunning Skyline Views from this North Loop condo.  Open layout with private balcony. Kitchen w/ updated countertops, backsplash, and lighting. New washer and dryer. California closet systems. Fresh paint throughout. Heated parking.  Steps away from Whole Foods, Twins Stadium, Target Station / LRT hub, Dog Park. Fulton Taproom, Smack Shack and many other shops/restaurants.  Common elements include rooftop deck, exercise and community room.

For sale: $1,895,000. Located along W River Pkwy in the North Loop of Downtown Minneapolis, this private neighborhood offers a
true sense of community, privacy, and quiet enjoyment within walking distance of award-winning
restaurants, cafes, shopping, parks, river pathways, light rail, sporting events, and more. This
remarkable home features river and skyline views, an open main living area with gas fireplace, three
bedrooms on one level, and master suite with a spa-like full bath and walk-in closet. Completely
renovated with thoughtful modern details for today's lifestyle. Enjoy a gourmet luxury kitchen featuring
modern stainless steel appliances, exhaust hood, custom cabinetry, and a large center island with
seating. Relax on the huge riverside deck which provides ample space for grilling, container gardening,
lounging, and outdoor entertaining. The second balcony offers skyline views. Spacious lower level with
wet bar, billiard area, storage, and natural daylight. Pristine heated garage w/storage.

For sale: $725,000. Experience the energy of North Loop and the historic beauty of Bookmen Lofts!  High ceilings, exposed brick plus fabulous views highlight this special corner city home.  Enjoy relaxing in your light filled open living area with gas FP and private deck - entertain in the kitchen and dining area w/ maple cabinetry,  granite countertops and center island.  Two spacious sunny bedrooms anchor at either corner of the loft, each w/private full bath and expansive closet.  A welcoming den and office area plus in home laundry complete this handsome home. Extra highlights include rooftop deck w/grills, fire pit and vibrant cityscapes plus underground parking and main level guest parking.  Work out in the fitness center, stroll to restaurants, shops, bakeries, entertainment, downtown, bike trails, the Mississppi and more.  This gem encompasses history and Minneapolis origins with a sleek and stunning interior. Take a tour, then make it your own!

For sale: $260,000. Please start your tour of 401 S. 1st. St. Enjoy this well cared for 1 bedroom condo in prime Riverwest building. This condo offers great entertaining space with open views from the kitchen through the living room and features updates in the kitchen and bath. Located in the heart of the Mill District allowing easy access to Stone Arch Bridge, Nicollet Island, the Guthrie and premier Twin Cities restaurants. Amenities include fitness center, party rooms & outdoor pool & grilling area & heated underground parking.

description: For sale: $234,000. Built from the ground up in 2007, 730 Lofts is the epitome of contemporary urban living in the North Loop. Located in the North Loop, 730 Lofts is close to amazing dining options, nightlife, sporting events, boutiques, and so much more!

description: For sale: $1,800,000. This custom, updated 3BR/3BA residence perches you above the Mississippi River w/views to the Stone Arch Bridge and Mill District. This spacious 2,282 sq ft unit has a stunning marble master BA remodel, redone powder BA, new appliances and more. Enjoy the river, grilling and eye-level firework displays from your 2 balconies. This Thoreau floor plan has gracious spaces, including large kitchen w/Sub-Zero French door refrigerator, Bosch Wall Oven and Microwave, Wolf Gas Cooktop and Miele Dishwasher. Master BA has been enhanced w/pocket doors to streamline the suite, which includes double vanity, private commode and walk in closet. Family rm captures the River, St. Anthony Falls and Stone Arch while still warming up with a gas fplc and mounted TV. 3rd BR is being used as an office. Amenities refresh underway, w/no assessment, to be complete early 2020. 1/2 block from the Skyway, The Carlyle (24-hr attendant, fitness, pool, guest suites, great room) offers premiere downtown living in the Mills District!

For sale: $3,195,000. Mill District one-of-a-kind loft penthouse in the historic North Star Lofts, a former woolen blanket mill on the National Registry of Historic Places. This spectacular home overlooks the mighty Mississippi River, St. Anthony Falls, and the Stone Arch Bridge. A private 26' x 22' rooftop deck with panoramic views is accessible directly from the unit. Custom, updated finishes throughout. Expansive open floor plan with soaring ceilings, oversized windows, light-filled living spaces, custom fireplace surround, and exposed limestone brick walls adding character and a sense of place against the dramatic riverfront views. A 3400 square foot corner plan that lives like a private townhome with three attached parking spaces and a secondary entrance. 3 bedrooms on one level, luxurious master suite with corner views, mezzanine-level den, upper level studio/office. 3 BR, 3 BA, 3 garage stalls. Storage. This is a must see and the first time it has been available on the open market.

description: Recently sold: $325,000. Location, Location, Location! Welcome to Tower Lofts where endless North Loop amenities are right out the front door. Never have to scrap your windshield thanks to a parking space in the heated garage, also with private storage! 2020-02-19

Parking stall 405 on P1; 24 hour attendant, outdoor pool, exercise room + Amenities refresh underway (see pictures of proposed updates), with no assessment, to be completed in early 2020.  3 guest apartments. Just ½ blk from the Skyway and steps to great restaurants, the Carlyle is a must see in the coveted Mill District.

Original exposed brick and timber columns provide coziness and the romance of the riverfront throughout the seasons. A very special home!

Enjoy the gym, outdoor pool and grill area, sauna, whirlpool.  Dog friendly!

description: Recently sold: $730,000. Absolutely stunning 6th floor condo in the North Loop, with remarkable unobstructed skyline views of downtown! Large east facing windows highlight the natural maple hardwood flooring throughout the home. This unit was built out from scratch, demonstrated by custom high-end upgrades throughout entire unit. Preparing meals is a pleasure in the oversized luxury kitchen, with custom granite countertops, and high-end stainless steal appliances, including gas range and wall oven. Morning coffee has never been better, sitting on your private patio, watching the sunrise over downtown Minneapolis. This condo is one of few two bedroom master suites, which each include large walk-in closets and full bathrooms. Master bedroom closet has been upgraded with ???California Closets Systems??? to give it a special touch. Walk to noteworthy award-winning restaurants, Target Field, Whole Foods, local shops, West River Parkway and the Greenway Trails. This is the luxury condo you've been waiting for!

description:
Recently sold: $265,000. Contact me to set up a showing: 612.325.5360 or Travis@NortonRealty.com. 

Live in North Loop, the hottest area of downtown Minneapolis, but just one block off Washington so it?s still peaceful. Originally built in 1917, this top floor unit features a recently rehabbed kitchen, a bathroom with deep soaking tub, exposed brick, concrete floors, gas fireplace, in-unit laundry, large floor to ceiling windows, and a private balcony. The modern galley kitchen has granite counter tops w/ breakfast bar and stainless steel appliances. Nice open floor plan and pet friendly building! One reserved heated indoor parking space and a storage unit included. This mixed use building includes commercial space, updated lobby and workout facility. Dining, sports & entertainment all within walking distance, including the light rail stop at Target Field.  Professionally managed. This property requires portfolio financing or cash to purchase.

description:
For rent: $1,975. Live in a classic River Towers condominium! This condo is spacious, has lots of closets, wood floors in common areas, and large area for a dining table and chairs. There are cable outlets in LR and both BRs. The large windows face southwest for great sunlight and beautiful views of the Minneapolis skyline. And the windows open wide for great breezes. This is an extraordinarily well-built and well-maintained building with friendly and helpful staff, package service, recycling center, and indoor car wash. Great location (Hennepin) for quick access to many buses and light rail. Walk to three grocery stores and endless restaurants and bars, enjoy the Mississippi River one block away, cross it to visit the St. Anthony Main neighborhood. Grill, swim, or hang out in the largest and most beautiful courtyard (the whole block) in downtown Minneapolis.

Tenant pays for electricity ($35-$40) and optional internet (free wifi is available in the building's public spaces). Owner pays for all other utilities including basic cable TV. Deposit amount includes a non-refundable $150 tenant move-in fee, which is required by the condo association. Parking is separately contracted with the condo association and costs $55 for off street and $90 for underground garage.

description: Recently sold: $1,000,000. Do you like sunny exposures & gorgeous city views from one of the most notable residential buildings in the Mill District? If so, you will love the Stone Arch Lofts! This corner location is freshly painted & is meticulously cared for & updated. Custom casework throughout, new lighting, artisan stonework, renovated kitchen, hardwood floors, private balcony, large laundry/pantry & serene spa-like owners bath make this an excellent value. Community roof deck featuring sweeping river views!

Recently sold: $370,000. Enchanting river front 1 BR/1 BA condo on Nicollet Island. Unique unit with exposed brick and wood beam ceilings, updated kitchen and bath with heated floors. 1 garage + 1 parking space. Walk or bike to everything! Enjoy the patio and tranquility right out your front door. Watch the ever changing Mississippi River vista, so peaceful, watching nature, the flow of the river is mesmerizing. Enjoy the changing of the seasons: winter boasts beautiful skyline views of Minneapolis and summer surrounding verdant parks. Listen to horse drawn carriages outside your window - a truly peaceful sound of the clippity clop of the horses! There is wildlife on the island including foxes, deer and rabbits, all which make for a truly unique, close-knit neighborhood. Great bicycling and walkability with the Heritage Trail that loops to the Stone Arch Bridge. Free music in the park at Nicollet Pavilion, walk to Boom Island Park and more!
